lion-->\n|evolution=N/A\n|stamina=209\n|attack=192\n|defense=229\n|fast={{m|Metal Claw}}, {{m|Zen Headbutt}}\n|special={{m|Close Combat}}, {{m|Iron Head}}, {{m|Stone Edge}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{Evobox-1\n|type1=Steel\n|type2=Fighting\n|pictype=art\n|no1=638\n|name1=Cobalion\n|type1-1=Steel\n|type2-1=Fighting\n}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=steel|type2=fighting}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=638}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=638}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=638}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|638|Cobalion}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Of the [[Swords of Justice]], Cobalion is the only one with a type immunity, the only one which has a double resistance, the only one whose English name is different from the official romanization of its Japanese name, and the only one whose French and German names differ from each other.\n\n===Origin===\nCobalion appears to be based on the character of {{wp|Athos (character)|Athos}} from the novel \'\'{{wp|The Three Musketeers}}\'\'. Like Athos, Cobalion is the oldest and the \'\'de facto\'\' leader of the group. Like the others of its trio, its appearance is based on {{wp|ungulate}}s. It bears close resemblance to a {{wp|markhor}} (a type of goat) and species of antelope such as the {{wp|greater kudu}} or {{wp|common eland}}. It also resembles a {{wp|Deer|stag}}. Like the other members of its trio, its nose is shaped like that of a {{wp|sheep}} or {{wp|goat}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nCobalion and Cobalon may be a combination of \'\'cobalt\'\' ({{wp|cobalt|a metal}} and {{wp|cobalt blue|a color}}) and \'\'stallion\'\' or \'\'champion\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=steel|type2=fighting\n|ja=コバルオン \'\'Cobalon\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'{{wp|cobalt}}\'\' and possibly \'\'champion\'\'\n|fr=Cobaltium|frmeaning=From \'\'cobalt\'\' and the suffix \'\'-ium\'\'\n|es=Cobalion|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Kobalium|demeaning=From {{tt|\'\'Kobalt\'\'|cobalt}} and the suffix \'\'-ium\'\'\n|it=Cobalion|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=코바르온 \'\'Cobalon\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=勾帕路翁 \'\'Gōupàlùwēng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|ru=Кобалион \'\'Kobalion\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Swords of Justice (M15)#Cobalion|Cobalion (M15)]]\n* [[Cobalion (Rumble Blast)]]\n* [[Swords of Justice]]\n* [[Swords of Justice (Adventures)]]\n\n==Notes==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{Legendary Pokémon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Steel|type2=Fighting}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Steel|prevnum=637|prev=Volcarona|nextnum=639|next=Terrakion}}\n|}\n{{-}}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Legendary Pokémon]]\n[[Category:Legendary Pokémon obtainable before the Elite Four]]\n[[Category:Trio masters]]\n[[Category:Unova Legendary Pokémon]]\n\n[[de:Kobalium]]\n[[es:Cobalion]]\n[[fr:Cobaltium]]\n[[it:Cobalion]]\n[[ja:コバルオン]]\n[[zh:勾帕路翁]]'}